Bisphenol A is a chemical used in making plastic bottles and most other plastic
products we use every day.  Until now, the only indication that bisphenol A, or
BPA, might be harmful came from studies using laboratory animals. Now, a study
involving humans indicates exposure to the chemical may increase the risk of
developing heart disease, diabetes and liver problems.  VOA's Carol Pearson has
more. 
 
 
 
 
 
